---
description: Use pcbridge to control open PlayCanvas Editor tabs from Cursor.
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

Use `pcbridge` for PlayCanvas Editor automation. Do not use DevTools, mouse/keyboard browser automation, or raw console typing.

Setup checks:

```bash
pcbridge doctor
pcbridge daemon status
pcbridge targets
```

If needed, ask the user to run `pcbridge daemon start`. If no target appears, ask them to run `pcbridge install-extension`, load the printed extension directory in `chrome://extensions`, and refresh PlayCanvas Editor.

Prefer structured commands:

```bash
pcbridge entity list --target current --limit 50
pcbridge entity patch --target current --id <resource_id> --set name=Player
pcbridge asset list --target current --type script
pcbridge script set-text --target current --asset-id <id> --file ./script.js
pcbridge viewport capture --target current --out /tmp/playcanvas.webp
```

Use `pcbridge eval` only for custom Editor API work. Snippets run with `editor`, `pc`, `pcui`, `window`, `document`, `command`, and `serialize`. Return compact JSON; never return raw `editor`, `Entity`, `Asset`, or app objects.
